---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Contact | burninjurycalc.com';
const description = 'How to reach the editorial team at burninjurycalc.com for corrections, citations, interview requests, and general feedback.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Contact</h1>

  <p>The editorial team welcomes corrections, citation suggestions, interview requests, and general feedback. We don't provide legal advice and don't review individual cases.</p>

  <h2>Editorial inquiries</h2>
  <p>Email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>
  <p>Please include the page URL when reporting a correction. We respond within a few business days.</p>

  <h2>What we can help with</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Corrections to published content (factual errors, outdated citations, broken links).</li>
    <li>Citation suggestions (peer-reviewed burn-medicine sources, recent appellate opinions, new state legislation on disfigurement damages).</li>
    <li>Interview requests from journalists or researchers.</li>
    <li>General feedback about the site.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we can't help with</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Legal advice on your specific case (contact a burn-injury attorney).</li>
    <li>Medical advice about your burn (contact a verified burn center or your treating provider).</li>
    <li>Specific case valuations beyond the calculator's general ranges.</li>
    <li>Referrals to specific law firms, burn centers, or medical providers.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>If you've experienced a burn injury</h2>
  <p>The immediate priorities are care at a verified burn center, evidence preservation, and consultation with an experienced burn-injury attorney. See <a href="/guides/what-to-do-after-a-burn-injury">what to do after a burn injury</a> for practical step-by-step guidance.</p>
</BaseLayout>
